s>Louise</gtr:otherNames><gtr:surname>Gilmore</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role><gtr:role><gtr:name>FELLOW</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FE025080%2F1"><gtr:id>E3243370-A7F7-4862-96A1-E91BA0F67AA0</gtr:id><gtr:title>Exploring the changing role of advertising creatives in the UK advertising industry</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/E025080/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This study fills a number of important gaps in the current advertising and management knowledge by exploring the life histories of 34 advertising creatives in London, Edinburgh and Glasgow. Using detailed life histories gained through semi-structured interviews, the research explores the creatives? motivations, behaviours and work experiences and thereby significantly enhancing the current understanding of advertising creatives. In addition the study addresses two gaps in related literature fields. In the creativity literature, the lived experiences of advertising creatives, their field and culture were unexplored. In the advertising literature, researchers had not taken advantage of the creativity literature?s life history insights. &lt;/p> 
&lt;p>The central findings relate to the nature of the creatives? experience of their creativity, the importance of social class as understood and experienced by the creatives, the partnership between the art director and the copywriter, the redefinition of agency?client relationships, and the new creative challenge posed by media. These findings form the foundation of the post doctorate year. Specifically for conference and workshop papers, publications targeting top tier journals, building a practitioner and academic network, and as the basis for submission of an ESRC research proposal.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2008-07-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2007-08-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>67239</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>41EB8C8C-0D56-4EFA-B780-7C12EB4A64AC</gtr:id><gtr:title>Exploring the relationship between the childhood and adolescent years of advertising creatives and the development of their creativity</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/76f4b97c12cd9fc1c0b178216bda4815"><gtr:id>76f4b97c12cd9fc1c0b178216bda4815</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames> Barbara Townley (Author)</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2007-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>r_8655676595cb346b98</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>E